<head>MAST</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">桅竿</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>LONG VERTICAL BEAM FOR HANGING SAILS on, IN the MIDDLE of a SHIP.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The only word for a mast, exceedingly rare, is wéi 桅. Early China was not a great sailing nation.</p>
        </div>
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p>
<p>COMM 29. 船上掛帆的豎杆。二詞最早見於漢代。</p>
<p>桅，通稱，口語性較強。</p>
<p>檣，書面語色彩較濃。古漢語中 “ 桅 ” 的使用少於 “ 檣 ” ；一直到明代的口語語料中， “ 桅 ” 才在使用上占優勢。</p>
        </div>
